    description: "Three days in Varanasi allows you to go beyond the tourist trail and discover the deeper layers of this ancient city. While Days 1 and 2 cover the essential ghats, temples, and Sarnath, Day 3 takes you to fascinating off-beat experiences — the silk weaving villages where Banarasi sarees are created on handlooms, the historic Ramnagar Fort, and the ancient Chunar Fort.\n\nVaranasi is a city that reveals itself slowly. With 3 days, you have the luxury of watching multiple sunrises from the ghats, exploring hidden lanes at your own pace, and attending both the morning and evening aarti ceremonies. The third day's visit to a weaving village is a unique experience where you see master craftsmen creating sarees that can take months to complete.\n\nOur cab service ensures comfortable transfers between all attractions, especially for the Chunar Fort excursion which is 35 km from the city. The driver stays with you throughout, providing reliable transport in a city where navigation can be challenging for visitors.",
