    description: "Amritsar is a city of profound spiritual energy and patriotic fervor. Our 2-day itinerary takes you from the serene Golden Temple to the electrifying Wagah Border ceremony. The Golden Temple at dawn, with its golden reflection in the sacred pool, is one of India's most moving experiences.\n\nDay 1 immerses you in Amritsar's spiritual and historical core — the Golden Temple, Jallianwala Bagh memorial, Partition Museum, and the historic Gobindgarh Fort. Day 2 covers the city's temples and culminates with the spectacular Wagah Border flag-lowering ceremony.\n\nAmritsar's culinary scene is legendary, and our itinerary includes time for the city's famous food — from kulchas at century-old dhabas to the world's largest free kitchen (langar) at the Golden Temple. A cab ensures comfortable travel to Wagah Border (30 km) and between the city's spread-out attractions.",
