    description: "Ladakh is the ultimate frontier adventure — a high-altitude desert where turquoise lakes meet snow-capped peaks and ancient Buddhist monasteries cling to cliffsides. Our 7-day itinerary covers the essential Ladakh circuit — Leh's monasteries, Nubra Valley's sand dunes, the legendary Pangong Lake, and the pristine Tso Moriri.\n\nDay 1 is dedicated to acclimatization in Leh (11,500 ft) — a crucial step for high-altitude travel. Days 2-5 take you through the highlights — Khardung La pass, Nubra Valley's Bactrian camels, and the color-changing Pangong Lake. Day 6 visits the less-touristy Tso Moriri, and Day 7 wraps up with Leh's heritage.\n\nAn SUV is strongly recommended for Ladakh due to high-altitude passes, rough roads, and river crossings. Our experienced Ladakhi drivers know every pass and can handle the challenging terrain safely.",
